			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Just for fun, I tried to see if Elemental Draw works on charmed mob. Went to BoT, charmed an elemental and took him down to 30% hp using ED only.
<br />

<br />
It's relative fast also, considering you're doing 200dps manafree. As a comparison, Sun Vortex is average 193dps with ID4 focus. Of course it's a skew comparison, as with SV you usually have added pet dps as well, and CoAM is a 500 mana spell.
<br />

<br />
The question is if this could be used practically. Killing a charmed mob with ED would make it poof, so have to kill charm before finishing off mob. Then of course the summoned mobs are rather limited :/
<br />

<br />
I was thinking if this could be used in places like Takish LDoN, say when group having too many adds, would it be viable to unsuspend pet, charm, ED nuke, clicky break mezz (ie. Earthen Boots), and have group kill off mob. Somehow I doubt that ED itself cause any additional aggro, it is classified as a beneficial spell..
<br />

<br />
Ok, I know this is probably not a useful thing in combat, but you have to admit it's a rather fun idea. Charm, drain yer enemy dry, also gaining a 3hp/tick rescource as an added bonus.
<br />

<br />
One thing I wonder about.. if making a summoned mob poof in an LDoN slaughter adventure, would that still add to the kill counter?
<br />

<br />
Perhaps more practical would be when using a charmed mob as DPS. Fight with pet til it's low on HP, do a few extra EDs, break and let group kill it off at 5% hp.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
